item.title: {S-Unit} Help Thred - Post ALL your Questions HERE
item.dc:creator: @Tico135 Tico
item.description:
@Tico135 wrote:

[quote=“Tico135, post:1, topic:103597”][center][size=15pt][color=navy]Rules of this board[/size][/center]

[ul][li]No spamming. This means making useless polls, unnessecary posts, and posting in Capital letters. If you do this there is a 95% you will be ignored. Posting just a smiley is spam.[/li]
[li]No Flamming. This means no cursing or swearing at anyone. If they spam, do not flame them about spam. Instead, report it and leave it as is. The moderators will deal with it.[/li]
[li]Do not under any circumstances talk about “rep” in any way. It is against the Moparscape/Moparisthebest rules.[/li]
[li][color=red]Do not create “Help Threads” to help people as this is what the section is for.[/li]
[li]Before you post a question, I would request that you check these FAQ’s as well as the stickies, as this might answer your question.[/li]
[li]Do not ask for a tutorial. Look for it in the tutorials section.[/li]
[li]Do not post multiple threads about the same question.[/li]
[li]Do not “bump” or “double post” or thread to get people to read it. This is a big one. Most new people tend to do this a lot. It is highly annoying![/li]
[li]Do not ask if servers are online. Use the server advertisement section for a server as well as the server status page.[/li]
[li]Stay on-topic. Do not post something that has nothing to do with the question at hand.[/li]
[li]Do not post useless polls. Create a topic instead.[/li]
[li]Only questions pertaining to Moparscape should be in this section[/li]
[li]Do not post unless you have tried yourself first. If there isn’t anything you can try, then this doesn’t apply to you[/li][/ul]

Note: This is only a guideline. The moderators and administrators will inforce the rules. Since Mod Taharok has approved this, these are the rules.

[center][size=12pt][b]Failure to follow these rules could result in one of the following actions:
Warned
Moderated
Muted
Banned

If you follow these rules then you will be fine.[b][/size][/center][/quote]

Are you not willing to read or learn? If you could and had a desire to you would know that help threads are against the rules. People can make their own threads as long as they are following the rules. A specific thread is not needed. Never beg for a sticky. Stickies are given if they are nessecary. You are basically crying for rep. My message to everyone that cares about rep: Ignore it altogether. Somehow people seem to avoid the rules and continue to break them.
